    <nav class="nav">
      <a href="/" class="logo">
        <span class="logo-mark">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <rect x="1" y="1" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e"/>
            <rect x="11" y="1" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.5"/>
            <rect x="1" y="11" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.5"/>
            <rect x="11" y="11" width="8" height="8" rx="2" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.25"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
        <span>MyTaxCalcs</span>
      </a>
      <div class="nav-links">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/calculators">Calculators</a>
        <a href="/california-income-tax-calculator">States</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
      </div>
      <a class="nav-cta" href="/calculators">All Calculators</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <section class="calc-hero">
    <div class="calc-hero-inner">
      <div class="section-label">Freelance & Contractor Tax</div>
      <h1>Self-Employment Tax Calculator</h1>
      <p>Estimate Social Security and Medicare taxes for freelance, contractor, gig, or small business income.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="calc-main">
    <div class="calc-layout">
      <section class="calc-form-card">
        <div class="calc-form-header">
          <div class="calc-form-icon" style="background:#eff6ff; color:#2563eb;">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h2>Your Income Information</h2>
        </div>
        <form method="POST" action="/self-employment-tax-calculator" class="calc-form">
          <div class="form-group">
            <label>Tax Year</label>
            <select name="taxYear">
              <option value="2025" <%= form.taxYear === "2025" ? "selected" : "" %>>2025</option>
              <option value="2026" <%= form.taxYear === "2026" ? "selected" : "" %>>2026</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="form-group">
            <label>Gross Self-Employment Income</label>
            <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span>
            <input type="number" name="grossIncome" value="<%= form.grossIncome || '' %>" placeholder="75,000" required></div>
          </div>
          <div class="form-group">
            <label>Business Expenses</label>
            <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span>
            <input type="number" name="businessExpenses" value="<%= form.businessExpenses || '' %>" placeholder="15,000"></div>
          </div>
          <button type="submit" class="calc-submit-btn">Calculate Self-Employment Tax <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></button>
        </form>
      </section>

      <section class="calc-results-card">
        <div class="calc-form-header">
          <div class="calc-form-icon" style="background:#eff6ff; color:#2563eb;">
            <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h2>Estimated Results</h2>
        </div>
        <% if (!result) { %>
          <div class="results-empty">
            <svg width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
            <p>Enter your income and expenses to estimate self-employment tax.</p>
          </div>
        <% } else { %>
          <div class="results-grid">
            <div class="result-row"><span>Tax Year</span><strong><%= result.taxYear %></strong></div>
            <div class="result-row"><span>Gross Income</span><strong>$<%= Math.round(result.grossIncome).toLocaleString() %></strong></div>
            <div class="result-row"><span>Business Expenses</span><strong>$<%= Math.round(result.businessExpenses).toLocaleString() %></strong></div>
            <div class="result-row"><span>Net Profit</span><strong>$<%= Math.round(result.netProfit).toLocaleString() %></strong></div>
            <div class="result-row"><span>Amount Subject to SE Tax</span><strong>$<%= Math.round(result.seTaxableIncome).toLocaleString() %></strong></div>
            <div class="result-row"><span>Social Security Portion</span><strong>$<%= Math.round(result.socialSecurityTax).toLocaleString() %></strong></div>
            <div class="result-row"><span>Medicare Portion</span><strong>$<%= Math.round(result.medicareTax).toLocaleString() %></strong></div>
            <div class="result-row result-highlight owed">
              <span>Total Self-Employment Tax</span>
              <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.totalSelfEmploymentTax).toLocaleString() %></strong>
            </div>
            <div class="result-row"><span>Deductible Half of SE Tax</span><strong>$<%= Math.round(result.deductibleHalf).toLocaleString() %></strong></div>
            <div class="result-row"><span>Est. Quarterly Payment</span><strong>$<%= Math.round(result.estimatedQuarterlyPayment).toLocaleString() %></strong></div>
          </div>
        <% } %>
        <div class="results-disclaimer">
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
          Estimate only. Not tax, legal, accounting, or financial advice.
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="calc-content-wrapper">
      <section class="content seo-content">
        <p class="eyebrow dark">Self-Employment Tax Guide</p>
        <h2>How this self-employment tax calculator works</h2>
        <p>This calculator estimates self-employment tax for people who earn income as freelancers, independent contractors, gig workers, sole proprietors, or small business owners. It subtracts business expenses from gross self-employment income, estimates net profit, and calculates Social Security and Medicare tax.</p>
        <div class="seo-grid">
          <div class="seo-mini-card"><h3>What it includes</h3><p>Gross self-employment income, business expenses, estimated net profit, Social Security tax, Medicare tax, and total self-employment tax.</p></div>
          <div class="seo-mini-card"><h3>Quarterly planning</h3><p>The quarterly estimate divides self-employment tax by four to help with planning, but it does not replace IRS estimated tax calculations.</p></div>
          <div class="seo-mini-card"><h3>What it excludes</h3><p>Federal income tax, state tax, credits, deductions, penalties, additional Medicare tax, or every business tax situation.</p></div>
        </div>
        <h2>Self-employment tax FAQ</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item"><h3>What is self-employment tax?</h3><p>Self-employment tax is the Social Security and Medicare tax paid by people who work for themselves. It is separate from regular federal income tax.</p></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><h3>Who usually pays self-employment tax?</h3><p>Freelancers, independent contractors, sole proprietors, gig workers, and some small business owners may owe self-employment tax if they have net earnings from self-employment.</p></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><h3>Does this calculator include income tax?</h3><p>No. This page estimates self-employment tax only. You may also owe federal income tax, state income tax, and other taxes depending on your situation.</p></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><h3>Why is only part of net profit subject to self-employment tax?</h3><p>Self-employment tax is generally calculated on 92.35% of net earnings from self-employment. This calculator uses that general rule for planning estimates.</p></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><h3>Should I use this for filing taxes?</h3><p>No. Use this as an educational estimate only. For filing, use official IRS forms, tax software, or a qualified tax professional.</p></div>
        </div>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</p>
      </section>
      <section class="content related-calculators">
        <p class="eyebrow dark">Related Calculators</p>
        <h2>More tax calculators</h2>
        <div class="related-grid">
          <a href="/income-tax-calculator">Income Tax Calculator</a>
          <a href="/tax-refund-calculator">Tax Refund Calculator</a>
          <a href="/capital-gains-tax-calculator">Capital Gains Tax</a>
          <a href="/sales-tax-calculator">Sales Tax Calculator</a>
          <a href="/payroll-tax-calculator">Payroll Tax Calculator</a>
          <a href="/calculators">All Calculators</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer">
